<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Sprite Layering]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10744&amp;p=121821#p121821"><![CDATA[
I'm not aware of any programs that let you preview layered sprites... AFAIK, you have to draw them using your favorite (unconstrained) graphics editor (Paint, Photoshop, whatever), make two copies and erase from each copy the colors that don't belong, and then you convert the result to CHR. I might be wrong though, let's see if someone can recommend any tools.<br /><br />Be careful when creating layered sprites though, because the NES can only display 8 sprites in a row. If you do more than add a couple of colorful details on top of your characters, you'll end up with a flickerfest.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Sun Dec 01, 2013 7:15 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
